<section class="py-20 px-4 sm:px-6">
  <div class="max-w-6xl mx-auto">
    <h2 class="text-3xl sm:text-4xl font-bold text-center mb-4">
      One agent is easy. Five across three machines is not.
    </h2>
    <p class="text-text-muted text-center max-w-2xl mx-auto mb-12">
      The tools for managing coding agents are either too hands-on or too hands-off.
    </p>

    <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-3 gap-6">
      <!-- Too granular -->
      <div class="p-6 rounded-lg bg-bg-card border border-border">
        <div class="text-xs font-mono text-text-muted uppercase tracking-wider mb-3">Too granular</div>
        <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold mb-2">Claude Code CLI</h3>
        <p class="text-text-muted text-sm leading-relaxed">
          One terminal per session. SSH into each machine. Alt-tab between windows to check what's running. Works for one agent — falls apart at three.
        </p>
      </div>

      <!-- The sweet spot -->
      <div class="p-6 rounded-lg bg-bg-card border-2 border-accent">
        <div class="text-xs font-mono text-accent uppercase tracking-wider mb-3">The sweet spot</div>
        <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold mb-2">Marmy</h3>
        <p class="text-text-muted text-sm leading-relaxed">
          A native app that shows every session across every machine. Monitor, message, and manage your agents from your phone. No infrastructure required.
        </p>
      </div>

      <!-- Too abstracted -->
      <div class="p-6 rounded-lg bg-bg-card border border-border">
        <div class="text-xs font-mono text-text-muted uppercase tracking-wider mb-3">Too abstracted</div>
        <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold mb-2">Orchestration platforms</h3>
        <p class="text-text-muted text-sm leading-relaxed">
          YAML configs, cloud infrastructure, layers of abstraction. You wanted to manage a few agents, not deploy a platform.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
